		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "This paper proposes a novel context-aware method \r",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "for analyzing sentiment at the level of individual sentences . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Most existing machine learning approaches suffer from limitations in the modeling of complex linguistic structures across sentences \r",
			"relation": "contrast"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "and often fail to capture non-local contextual cues \r",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "that are important for sentiment interpretation . <S>\r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "In contrast , our approach allows structured modeling of sentiment \r",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "while taking into account both local and global contextual information . <S>\r",
			"relation": "temporal"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 6,
			"text": "Specifically , we encode intuitive lexical and discourse knowledge as expressive constraints \r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "and integrate them into the learning of conditional random field models \r",
			"relation": "progression"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "via posterior regularization . <S>\r",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "The context-aware constraints provide additional power to the CRF model \r",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 11,
			"text": "and can guide semi-supervised learning \r",
			"relation": "joint"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 12,
			"text": "when labeled data is limited . <S>\r",
			"relation": "condition"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "Experiments on standard product review datasets show \r",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
